.TH WORKCELL 1 "2026-03-22" "Workcell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
workcell \- bounded runtime launcher for coding agents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B workcell
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fB--\fR \fIprovider-args\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B workcell
starts the selected coding agent inside the Workcell runtime boundary.
The Tier 1 path is a dedicated Colima virtual machine profile on macOS plus a
hardened container inside that VM.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --agent codex|claude|gemini
Select the provider to run. The default is
.BR codex .
.TP
.B --ui cli|gui
Select the surface to launch. Only
.BR cli
is currently implemented as a preserved-boundary path.
.TP
.B --mode strict|build|breakglass
Select the runtime profile. The default is
.BR strict .
.TP
.B --workspace PATH
Select the workspace to mount inside the runtime. The default is the current
directory.
.TP
.B --allow-nongit-workspace
Allow a workspace without repository or agent marker files.
.TP
.B --colima-profile NAME
Override the derived Colima profile name.
.TP
.B --rebuild
Rebuild the runtime image before launch.
.TP
.B --dry-run
Print the selected runtime command and exit.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show usage information.
.SH PROFILES
.TP
.B strict
Allowlisted network access only, no host credential or control socket
passthrough, and the provider's bounded execution mode.
.TP
.B build
The same mount and secret restrictions as
.BR strict ,
with broader network access for dependency and build traffic.
.TP
.B breakglass
Still inside the Workcell VM plus container boundary, but with unrestricted
network access and the provider's highest-trust execution mode.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/workcell
Installed launcher path used by
.BR scripts/install.sh .
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/man/man1/workcell.1
Installed man page path used by
.BR scripts/install.sh .
.SH EXIT STATUS
The command exits non-zero on validation failures, unsupported modes, missing
dependencies, or runtime launch errors.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR colima (1),
.BR docker (1)
